The hidden information is often not published in any form

1602
01:18:14.635 --> 01:18:17.155
and must be requested through the Official Information Act.

1603
01:18:17.765 --> 01:18:19.495
Sometimes the data we require

1604
01:18:19.515 --> 01:18:22.095
to construct a comprehensive analysis on the performance

1605
01:18:22.095 --> 01:18:24.335
of fundamental aspects of our health system,

1606
01:18:24.875 --> 01:18:26.015
namely unmet need

1607
01:18:26.015 --> 01:18:28.295
and the health workforce is not routinely collected.

1608
01:18:29.085 --> 01:18:30.535
Data is often fragmented,

1609
01:18:30.775 --> 01:18:33.095
inconsistent if it's collected at all.

1610
01:18:34.395 --> 01:18:38.315
We regularly find gaps in published performance reporting,

1611
01:18:38.315 --> 01:18:40.395
which we would consider basic outcome measures.

1612
01:18:40.885 --> 01:18:43.595
These are things like the number of healthcare workers

1613
01:18:43.735 --> 01:18:46.675
by headcount and FTE in any hospital district

1614
01:18:46.775 --> 01:18:50.755
by professional group role or service, hospital bed numbers

1615
01:18:50.815 --> 01:18:51.915
and occupancy rates.

1616
01:18:52.265 --> 01:18:55.395
Emergency department capacity to cope with surges in demand

1617
01:18:56.275 --> 01:18:57.875
clinical thresholds for access to services,

1618
01:18:58.835 --> 01:19:01.715
clinical accountability and adverse events data.

1619
01:19:02.685 --> 01:19:04.225
And on this last point, we note

1620
01:19:04.225 --> 01:19:06.945
that Health New Zealand was not publishing adverse events

1621
