1647
01:20:11.995 --> 01:20:15.565
including health status, access to care, equity

1648
01:20:16.545 --> 01:20:21.005
or obligations, quality of care, health outcomes,

1649
01:20:21.105 --> 01:20:22.285
and system efficiency.

1650
01:20:23.155 --> 01:20:25.925
Data collected through the New Zealand Health Survey tracks

1651
01:20:25.975 --> 01:20:27.885
unmet need for primary care, dental care,

1652
01:20:28.025 --> 01:20:29.125
and for mental health care.

1653
01:20:30.245 --> 01:20:32.465
But there is currently no meaningful mechanism

1654
01:20:32.565 --> 01:20:34.425
to determine unmet need for hospital

1655
01:20:34.565 --> 01:20:36.145
and outpatient specialist care.

1656
01:20:37.015 --> 01:20:38.115
Our members inform us

1657
01:20:38.115 --> 01:20:40.395
that more referrals are being declined due

1658
01:20:40.395 --> 01:20:42.635
to workforce shortages and budget constraints.

1659
01:20:43.575 --> 01:20:45.555
We have recently found out that the number

1660
01:20:45.555 --> 01:20:48.275
of declined referrals are not being collated nationally,

1661
01:20:48.335 --> 01:20:50.475
so there's no overall picture of the scale

1662
01:20:50.495 --> 01:20:51.755
of need for planned care.

1663
01:20:52.825 --> 01:20:53.845
Our analysis shows

1664
01:20:53.845 --> 01:20:56.085
that waiting lists are effectively being managed

1665
01:20:56.145 --> 01:20:57.445
by declining referrals.

1666
01:20:58.105 --> 01:21:00.485
And the true wait list for a first specialist appointment

1667
01:21:00.485 --> 01:21:03.685
or treatment will far exceed available system capacity

1668
01:21:04.765 --> 01:21:06.955
First, first specialist appointment wait list.

1669
01:21:06.955 --> 01:21:08.355
Numbers are in fact flatlining

1670
01:21:08.355 --> 01:21:10.955
because the threshold to get on the wait list is so high

1671
01:21:11.895 --> 01:21:14.395
to improve our understanding of the total unmet need

1672
01:21:14.395 --> 01:21:18.435
for healthcare regular population surveys by age, ethnicity,

1673
01:21:18.655 --> 01:21:23.235
region deprivation, and disease prevalence are all critical.

1674
01:21:24.665 --> 01:21:27.635
Also critical is accurately reporting the iceberg

1675
01:21:27.635 --> 01:21:28.755
of planned care data.

1676
01:21:29.025 --> 01:21:31.195
This reporting must include information on

1677
01:21:31.215 --> 01:21:32.275
all patient journeys.

1678
01:21:32.705 --> 01:21:35.755
What is above the surface of the actual FSA wait list

1679
01:21:35.775 --> 01:21:38.515
and what is hidden below the surface being this being the

1680
01:21:38.515 --> 01:21:41.275
many thousands of people with their referrals declined.

