1684
01:21:50.975 --> 01:21:52.915
and levels of unmet health need.

1685
01:21:53.575 --> 01:21:55.555
The report analyzes nearly 15 years

1686
01:21:55.555 --> 01:21:58.195
of the self-reported health status question in the

1687
01:21:58.215 --> 01:21:59.395
New Zealand Health Survey.

1688
01:22:00.415 --> 01:22:01.795
She found that the proportion

1689
01:22:01.795 --> 01:22:05.675
of New Zealanders in excellent health is declining by 2036.

1690
01:22:05.735 --> 01:22:09.275
If current trends continue, there will be fewer than 7%

1691
01:22:09.275 --> 01:22:10.995
of New Zealanders in excellent health.

1692
01:22:11.775 --> 01:22:14.395
The proportion of New Zealanders in fair health is rising

1693
01:22:14.815 --> 01:22:17.795
and it is rising for people of working age

1694
01:22:18.505 --> 01:22:21.275
more than more than people over the age of 65.

1695
01:22:22.215 --> 01:22:24.195
People in fair health are much more likely

1696
01:22:24.295 --> 01:22:26.915
to require health services than people in excellent health.

1697
01:22:27.655 --> 01:22:30.355
And as fair health has increased in the population,

1698
01:22:30.895 --> 01:22:34.155
so has unmet need for primary care, mental health services,

1699
01:22:34.255 --> 01:22:35.275
and oral health care.

1700
01:22:36.965 --> 01:22:38.945
Moving to workforce, our experience

1701
01:22:38.945 --> 01:22:41.065
of publicly available workforce data is

1702
01:22:41.065 --> 01:22:43.105
that it is unreliable and incomplete.

1703
01:22:43.935 --> 01:22:45.745
Data on health workforce capacity

1704
01:22:45.745 --> 01:22:47.865
and capability is largely non-existent.

1705
01:22:48.565 --> 01:22:50.785
The size of the health workforce is not determined

1706
01:22:50.785 --> 01:22:54.065
by current demand or unmet need for care, but by budgets.

1707
01:22:55.445 --> 01:22:58.505
Our systems do not enable meaningful planning, budgeting,

1708
01:22:58.505 --> 01:23:00.145
or forecasting for the health workforce

1709
01:23:00.405 --> 01:23:02.825
and do not account for demand or unmet need.

1710
01:23:03.455 --> 01:23:05.525
Some systems such as rostering

1711
01:23:05.525 --> 01:23:07.685
and scheduling still require paper reports.

1712
01:23:09.195 --> 01:23:11.835
Ultimately what this means is a system run on the goodwill

1713
01:23:11.835 --> 01:23:14.075
of health workers to cover entrenched shortages.

1714
01:23:15.255 --> 01:23:17.595
We note that the recently announced digital health

1715
01:23:17.595 --> 01:23:19.635
investment plan includes a component

1716
01:23:19.655 --> 01:23:22.035
for a human capital management system that seek

1717
01:23:22.035 --> 01:23:23.595
to address some of these issues,

1718
01:23:23.625 --> 01:23:25.875
including workforce planning and rostering.

1719
01:23:27.005 --> 01:23:28.875
While this is a welcome development,

1720
01:23:28.875 --> 01:23:30.755
these are urgently needed upgrades,

1721
01:23:30.755 --> 01:23:33.715
which will still take 10 years to be operational according

1722
01:23:33.735 --> 01:23:34.875
to the plans timeline.

1723
01:23:36.095 --> 01:23:37.395
Our surveys and analysis

1724
01:23:37.395 --> 01:23:39.035
of the senior medical workforce reveal

1725
01:23:39.035 --> 01:23:41.595
that doctors are struggling to cover for absent colleagues,

1726
01:23:42.145 --> 01:23:44.795
provide appropriate time and training to registrars,

1727
01:23:45.095 --> 01:23:47.355
and have time to provide patient-centered care

1728
01:23:47.775 --> 01:23:51.395
to patients in whanau as demand for care grows.

1729
01:23:51.845 --> 01:23:54.995
These measures must be part of any public accountability

1730
01:23:55.095 --> 01:23:56.155
or performance reporting.

1731
01:23:56.375 --> 01:23:57.795
We do not have a workforce target

1732
01:23:58.535 --> 01:24:01.555
nor measurable workforce recruitment and retention goals.

1733
01:24:02.575 --> 01:24:05.315
The health workforce takes up about two thirds

1734
01:24:05.315 --> 01:24:06.555
of operational spending.

1735
01:24:07.175 --> 01:24:10.115
The ability of that workforce to work most effectively

1736
01:24:10.495 --> 01:24:13.875
and efficiently is the make or break of the health system.

1737
01:24:14.735 --> 01:24:16.955
We strongly recommend developing a regular

1738
01:24:17.795 --> 01:24:20.755
publicly reported comprehensive health workforce census.

1739
01:24:21.465 --> 01:24:22.835
This could not only serve

1740
01:24:22.975 --> 01:24:25.235
to fill the data gaps on workforce numbers,

1741
01:24:25.775 --> 01:24:29.315
but also provide valuable qualitative insights into job

1742
01:24:29.675 --> 01:24:32.395
satisfaction and where changes needed in a dynamic

1743
01:24:32.655 --> 01:24:34.355
and constantly evolving system.

1744
01:24:35.375 --> 01:24:37.835
In summary, the gaps in health performance reporting

1745
01:24:37.915 --> 01:24:39.675
and accountability data are stark

1746
01:24:40.095 --> 01:24:42.355
and baseline information on unmet need

1747
01:24:42.775 --> 01:24:45.155
and the health workforce does not exist.

1748
01:24:46.015 --> 01:24:48.635
We urgently need to address these gaps in order

1749
01:24:48.655 --> 01:24:50.035
to improve the efficiency

1750
01:24:50.335 --> 01:24:52.755
and effectiveness of the health system outcomes

1751
01:24:52.855 --> 01:24:54.995
for patients, and to develop a health workforce

1752
01:24:54.995 --> 01:24:56.275
that has the capacity

1753
01:24:56.495 --> 01:24:59.115
and capability to meet our growing health needs.

